            . I live at <placeName id="t18220220-170-crimeloc922">Poplar</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220220-170-crimeloc922" type="placeName" value="Poplar"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220220-170-crimeloc922" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220220-170-off920 t18220220-170-crimeloc922"></join>, and am a <rs id="t18220220-170-viclabel923" type="occupation">labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220220-170-victim1575 t18220220-170-viclabel923"></join>. On the 3d of January, I went home, and missed my coat at half-past nine o'clock at night; a strange man had slept in the same room - I left him in bed. Next morning I found it had been pawned, and redeemed again. On the Tuesday following, I saw it hanging up for sale in Ratcliff-highway, and got an officer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220220-170-person1577">
                  MARY 
                  STILES
               <interp inst="t18220220-170-person1577" type="surname" value="STILES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-170-person1577" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-170-person1577" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at Poplar. Chandler lodges with me; he lost his coat on the 2d of January - the prisoner slept in the room over night, with him and another man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220220-170-person1578">
                  NOAH 
                  GOULSTON
               <interp inst="t18220220-170-person1578" type="surname" value="GOULSTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-170-person1578" type="given" value="NOAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-170-person1578" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a slopseller, and live in Ratcliff-highway. The prisoner came to me on the 3d of January, with the duplicate of the coat, which was pawned for 6 s., he wanted 3 s. for it - I bought it, and redeemed it. I am sure he is the man; he came again, in about a week, with a duplicate - I detained him; he said he stole the coat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220220-170-person1579">
